@startuml
' Author: Nicholas Irvine  GitHub https://github.com/SaladStik  LinkedIn https://www.linkedin.com/in/nicholas-irvine-303ab5284/
title Orbit Only nginx is Exposed

' There is exactly one door into the system. Every other
' service lives on a private network and you cannot reach it from outside.

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false

actor "Browser\n(outside world)" as browser

rectangle "Public surface" #ffe9e9 {
  component "nginx\n:80 -> :443 (HTTPS)" as nginx
}

rectangle "Internal network 'orbit'\n(no public ports)" #e9f5ff {
  component "ui" as ui
  component "auth" as auth
  component "node-gateway" as gw
  component "python-worker" as worker
  component "Redis" as redis
  queue "Kafka" as kafka
  database "Postgres" as pg
  component "Debezium" as dbz
}

browser --> nginx : the ONLY way in (HTTPS)

nginx --> ui
nginx --> auth
nginx --> gw

auth --> redis
gw --> kafka
gw --> pg
worker --> kafka
worker --> pg
pg --> dbz
dbz --> kafka

note right of nginx : In Compose only nginx maps a port. In k8s NetworkPolicy enforces it.
note bottom of worker : Nothing internal is published.

@enduml
